&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Product Marketing Manager at Pushpay you will be responsible for supporting the development and execution of differentiated GTM plans that speak to the needs of our customers, and coordinate how those GTM plans integrate with enablement assets, marketing campaigns, website updates and other customer facing assets. This role sits at the critical intersection between Product, Marketing, Sales and Customer Success, and is accountable for ensuring Pushpay’s product positioning, messaging and storytelling is boldly articulated to both customers and prospects to support growth in competitive positioning, sales, product adoption, and customer retention.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting to the Director of Product Marketing and a key member of the Product Marketing and Creative Production team, this role can be based in Colorado Springs or remote, where you’ll collaborate with people from all functions and our marketing leadership team every day, while working to help our customers—churches, parishes, and non-profit customers—achieve their mission.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we’re looking for in the ideal candidate:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an experienced and dynamic product marketing professional that is a team player, a self-starter with a bias for action and the desire to bring creativity and out-of-the-box thinking to support the Product Marketing Team. The ideal candidate has experience conducting competitive research, developing compelling sales enablement materials grounded in accurate and differentiated positioning, and producing customer evidence that demonstrates real-world value. They are skilled at leveraging AI to accelerate research, content development, and execution, allowing them to focus on what matters most: uncovering insights, crafting compelling stories, and communicating customer impact.&lt;/p&gt;
